    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so you're saying it's basically a failure because of the veto power? i've seen some people argue that the UN is actually pretty indispensable and that without it the world would be way more chaotic. do historians see those people as being right, or is the \"failure\" argument more of the mainstream view?",
